17/05/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- At the weekend, Sofia hosted an international forum titled "Culture:
A Stability Factor in Southeast Europe".
The forum, which began on Friday (14 May), was the first of its kind to be held at the parliamentary culture committee level.
Attending were representatives of Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Greece, Macedonia, Romania, Serbia-Montenegro, Slovenia, Turkey and Bulgaria.
Participants agreed to host the event on a rotating basis.
(BTA - 15/05/04)
